cs.CG, cs.DS, cs.DM, cs.NA, cs.AI. 

The paper deals with computational geometry problems related to rectangles in 2D, which suggests cs.CG (Computational Geometry) as the most likely sub-category. The use of greedy algorithms and approximation ratios suggests cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) as other likely sub-categories. The mention of the size of independent set and the clique cover being tightly bounded by $\sqrt{n}$ suggests cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) as another possible sub-category. Finally, the mention of refined greedy algorithms and the possibility of a provably constant factor approximation algorithm suggests cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as a possible sub-category.
